webNMSVersion.name: webNMSVersion
webNMSVersion.description: The version number of the AdventNet WebNMS System.

webNMSHost.name: webNMSHost
webNMSHost.description: The hostname of the system in which the AdventNet WebNMS system is executed on.

webNMSIpAddress.name: webNMSIpAddress
webNMSIpAddress.description: The ipaddress of the system in which the AdventNet WebNMS system is executed on.

webNMSTotalMemory.name: webNMSTotalMemory
webNMSTotalMemory.description: The Total memory of the device in which the WebNMS is running

webNMSFreeMemory.name: webNMSFreeMemory
webNMSFreeMemory.description: The Free memory available in the device in which the WebNMS is running

webNMSStartTime.name: webNMSStartTime
webNMSStartTime.description: This variable states the time at which the NMS Server started

webNMSUpTime.name: webNMSUpTime
webNMSUpTime.description: This variable states the duration for which the NMS Server has been running

webNMSShutdown.name: webNMSShutdown
webNMSShutdown.description: This variable is used to shutdown the NMS from the manager. The user needs to give the login name and the password.Once,the user gives the loginname and the password,the NMS Server shuts down. SYNTAX: loginName,password

webNMSSchedulerTable.name: webNMSSchedulerTable
webNMSSchedulerTable.description: A table of WebNMS scheduler instances

webNMSSchedulerEntry.name: webNMSSchedulerEntry
webNMSSchedulerEntry.description: A collection of objects specific to the WebNMS system Scheduler

webNMSSchedulerIndex.name: webNMSSchedulerIndex
webNMSSchedulerIndex.description: The index for the WebNMS Scheduler instance

webNMSSchedulerDesc.name: webNMSSchedulerDesc
webNMSSchedulerDesc.description: A description of the WebNMS Scheduler instance

webNMSSchedulerNumTasks.name: webNMSSchedulerNumTasks
webNMSSchedulerNumTasks.description: The number of tasks scheduled in this WebNMS Scheduler instance

webNMSSchedulerNumThreads.name: webNMSSchedulerNumThreads
webNMSSchedulerNumThreads.description: Total number of Worker threads available

webNMSSchedulerActiveThreads.name: webNMSSchedulerActiveThreads
webNMSSchedulerActiveThreads.description: The number of active Worker threads

webNMSSchedulerIdleThreads.name: webNMSSchedulerIdleThreads
webNMSSchedulerIdleThreads.description: The number of idle Worker threads

webNMSNumObjects.name: webNMSNumObjects
webNMSNumObjects.description: The number of objects being managed by the AdventNet WebNMS system.

webNMSNumNetworks.name: webNMSNumNetworks
webNMSNumNetworks.description: The number of networks being managed by the AdventNet WebNMS system.

webNMSNumNodes.name: webNMSNumNodes
webNMSNumNodes.description: The number of nodes being managed by the AdventNet WebNMS system.

webNMSNumInterfaces.name: webNMSNumInterfaces
webNMSNumInterfaces.description: The number of interfaces being managed by the AdventNet WebNMS system.

moUserPropNames.name: moUserPropNames
moUserPropNames.description: This variable indicates to the agent what all user property values the user would like to see in the moUserProp variable of the MoTable. This also provides for the facility of viewing all the user property-values by specifying the word 'all' . If the user needs to see only a few specific user property values ,then he needs to specify them explicitly SYNTAX1 all SYNTAX2 userPropName1,userPropName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPopName2=value2..

moTable.name: moTable
moTable.description: This describes the details of Managed Objects

moEntry.name: moEntry
moEntry.description: An entry of the Mo Table

moNameIndex.name: moNameIndex
moNameIndex.description: This variable represents the name of the Network Element. This name should uniquely represent the MO in the network domain across all MO types.This entry corresponds to the Name field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moOwnerName.name: moOwnerName
moOwnerName.description: This variable represents the Ownername of the Network Element. This name also uniquely represents the MO in the network domain across all MO types. This entry corresponds to the OwnerName field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moType.name: moType
moType.description: This variable represents the type of the Network Element whose attributes are presented in this specific row of the MO table.This entry corresponds to the Type field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moFailureCount.name: moFailureCount
moFailureCount.description: This variable represents the number of failures occuring in the network element. This entry corresponds to the FailureCount field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moFailureThreshold.name: moFailureThreshold
moFailureThreshold.description: This variable represents the minimum value for failures which acts as the threshold.This entry corresponds to the FailureThreshold field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moManaged.name: moManaged
moManaged.description: This variable states whether the mo is managed or not.This entry corresponds to the Managed field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moStatus.name: moStatus
moStatus.description: This value gives the current status of the MO.This entry corresponds to the Status field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moStatusChangeTime.name: moStatusChangeTime
moStatusChangeTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the status of the mo was formally acknowledged to have changed.This entry corresponds to the StatusChangeTime field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moStatusUpdateTime.name: moStatusUpdateTime
moStatusUpdateTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the status of the mo was formally acknowledged to have been updated.This entry corresponds to the StatusUpdateTime field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moPollInterval.name: moPollInterval
moPollInterval.description: This variable states the polling interval of the mo.This entry corresponds to the PollInterval field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moUserProperties.name: moUserProperties
moUserProperties.description: The values for the user properties which the user specifies in the moUserPropNames variable are displayed The values will be displayed in the folloing formate propName1=value1,porpName2=vaule2,....

moDerivedProperties.name: moDerivedProperties
moDerivedProperties.description: This variable displays the values of the user defined objects ' properties which the user specifies in the derivedPropNames variable in the moDerivedPropNamesTable. The values will be displayed in the following formate propName1=value1,propName2=value2,....

inheritingOid1.name: inheritingOid1
inheritingOid1.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is derived from TopoObject, then, the oid of the TopoObjectTable in this MIB will be filled here.If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName1.name: inheritingTableName1
inheritingTableName1.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is derived from TopoObject, then, the table name TopoObjectTable will be filled here.If the tablename is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

topoObjTable.name: topoObjTable
topoObjTable.description: This table contains the various topo Objects

topoObjEntry.name: topoObjEntry
topoObjEntry.description: An entry of the topoObject Table

ipAddress.name: ipAddress
ipAddress.description: This variable states the ipAddress of the Object.This entry corresponds to the IpAddress field of the TopoObject table in the database

netmask.name: netmask
netmask.description: This variable states the net mask of the object.This entry corresponds to the NetMask field of the TopoObject table in the database

moCommunity.name: moCommunity
moCommunity.description: This variable states the read community String used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an SnmpNode.This entry corresponds to the Community field of the TopoObject table in the database

moWriteCommunity.name: moWriteCommunity
moWriteCommunity.description: This variable states the write community String used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an SnmpNode.This entry corresponds to the WriteCommunity field of the TopoObject table in the database

snmpPort.name: snmpPort
snmpPort.description: This variable states the Snmp port used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an Snmp Node.This entry corresponds to the SnmpPort field of the TopoObject table in the database

isDHCP.name: isDHCP
isDHCP.description: This variable states whether the network element supports DHCP (i.e is the ipaddress for the network element assigned by DHCP protocol). This entry corresponds to the IsDHCP field of the TopoObject table in the database

baseMibs.name: baseMibs
baseMibs.description: This variable states the Mibs implemented by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an Snmp Node.This entry corresponds to the BaseMibs field of the TopoObject table in the database

version.name: version
version.description: This variable states the version used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This entry corresponds to the Version field of the TopoObject table in the database.

userName.name: userName
userName.description: This variable states the userName used by the SNMPv3 Agent in the Network Element. This entry corresponds to the UserName field of the TopoObject table in the database.

contextName.name: contextName
contextName.description: This variable states the contextName used by the SNMPv3 Agent in the Network Element. This entry corresponds to the ContextName field of the TopoObject table in the database.

inheritingOid2.name: inheritingOid2
inheritingOid2.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either Node or any of its child, then, the oid of the NodeTable in this MIB will be filled here.If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName2.name: inheritingTableName2
inheritingTableName2.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either Node or any of its child, then, the table name NodeTable will be filled here.If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

networkTable.name: networkTable
networkTable.description: This table contains information about the various networks supported by the NMS

networkEntry.name: networkEntry
networkEntry.description: An entry of the Network table

discover.name: discover
discover.description: This variable states whether disocvery is being done on this network or not. This entry corresponds to the Discover field of the Network table in the database

discoverStatus.name: discoverStatus
discoverStatus.description: This variable states the discovery status for the network. This entry corresponds to the DiscoveryStatus field of the Network table in the database

inheritingOid3.name: inheritingOid3
inheritingOid3.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MyNetworkChild) of Network (or any child of MyNetworkChild),then, the oid of the direct child's table (e.g. MyNetworkChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here, If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName3.name: inheritingTableName3
inheritingTableName3.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MyNetworkChild) of Network (or any child of MyNetworkChild),then, the tablename of the direct child's table (e.g. MyNetworkChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here, If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

nodeTable.name: nodeTable
nodeTable.description: This table describes the nodes in the NMS

nodeEntry.name: nodeEntry
nodeEntry.description: An entry of the Node table

isRouter.name: isRouter
isRouter.description: This variable states whether the node is a router or not. This entry corresponds to the isRouter field of the Node table in the database

inheritingOid4.name: inheritingOid4
inheritingOid4.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpNode or any of its child, then, the oid of the SnmpNodeTable in this MIB will be filled here. If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName4.name: inheritingTableName4
inheritingTableName4.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpNode or any of its child, then, the tabel name SnmpNodeTable will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

ipAddressTable.name: ipAddressTable
ipAddressTable.description: This table describes the ipAddress objects

ipAddressEntry.name: ipAddressEntry
ipAddressEntry.description: An entry of the ipAddress table

parentNode.name: parentNode
parentNode.description: This variable states the parent Node of this Interface.This entry corresponds to the ParentNode field of the IpAddress table in the database.

parentNet.name: parentNet
parentNet.description: This variable states the name of the parent network to which this Interface belongs. This entry corresponds to the ParentNode field of the IpAddress table in the database.

inheritingOid5.name: inheritingOid5
inheritingOid5.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpInterface or any of its child.Then,the oid of the SnmpInterfaceTable in this MIB will be filled here. If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName5.name: inheritingTableName5
inheritingTableName5.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpInterface or any of its child.Then,the tabelname SnmpInterfaceTable will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

snmpNodeTable.name: snmpNodeTable
snmpNodeTable.description: This table describes the SNMP nodes in the WebNMS

snmpNodeEntry.name: snmpNodeEntry
snmpNodeEntry.description: An entry of the snmpNode table

hostNetMask.name: hostNetMask
hostNetMask.description: This variable states the netmask of the primary interface reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the HostNetMask field of the SnmpNode table in the database

sysDesc.name: sysDesc
sysDesc.description: This variable states the System Descriptor of this node as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the SysDescr field of the SnmpNode table in the database

sysName.name: sysName
sysName.description: This variable states the System Name of this node as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the SysName field of the SnmpNode table in the database

sysOid.name: sysOid
sysOid.description: This variable states the System Object Identifier of this node as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the SysOid field of the SnmpNode table in the database

inheritingOid6.name: inheritingOid6
inheritingOid6.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child ( e.g. MySnmpNodeChild) of SnmpNode (or any child of MySnmpNodeChild),then, the oid of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpNodeChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName6.name: inheritingTableName6
inheritingTableName6.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child ( e.g. MySnmpNodeChild) of SnmpNode (or any child of MySnmpNodeChild),then, the table name of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpNodeChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

snmpInterfaceTable.name: snmpInterfaceTable
snmpInterfaceTable.description: This table describes the properties of the snmp interfaces attached to a Snmp node disocvered by the WebNMS system.

hostnetMask.name: hostnetMask
hostnetMask.description: This variable states the netmask of this interface reported by the snmp agent in the node to which this interface object is attahced. This entry corresponds to the HostNetMask field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

ifIndex.name: ifIndex
ifIndex.description: This variable states the interface index reported by the snmp agent in the node to which this interface object is attached. This entry corresponds to the IfIndex field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

physMedia.name: physMedia
physMedia.description: This variable states the physical media of this inetrface as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the PhysMedia field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

physAddress.name: physAddress
physAddress.description: This variable states the Physical address of the interface as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the PhysAddr field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

ifSpeed.name: ifSpeed
ifSpeed.description: This variable states the speed of this interface as reported by the snmp agent.This entry corresponds to the IfSpeed field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

ifDesc.name: ifDesc
ifDesc.description: This variable states the descriptor of this inetrface as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the IfDescr field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

sysOID.name: sysOID
sysOID.description: This variable states the System Object Identifier of this node as reported by the snmp agent.This entry corresponds to the SysOid field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

inheritingOid7.name: inheritingOid7
inheritingOid7.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChild) of SnmpInterface (or any child of MySnmpInterfaceChild),then, the oid of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName7.name: inheritingTableName7
inheritingTableName7.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChild) of SnmpInterface (or any child of MySnmpInterfaceChild),then, the table name of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

moDerivedPropNameTable.name: moDerivedPropNameTable
moDerivedPropNameTable.description: This table contains the type of the user-defined objects and the properties of the user defined objects. The user can specify what all user-object's properties he wants to be displayed in the moDerivedProperties in MO table.

moDerivedPropNameEntry.name: moDerivedPropNameEntry
moDerivedPropNameEntry.description: An entry of the User Object Table.

indexNum.name: indexNum
indexNum.description: This variable is an incremental integer which uniquely identifies each entry of the table.

objClassName.name: objClassName
objClassName.description: This variable indicates the class name of the user defined objects and identifies them uniquely.The user needs to specify the full package name of the object For example : com.adventnet.nms.topodb.Node

derivedPropNames.name: derivedPropNames
derivedPropNames.description: This variable indicates the names of the derived properties of user defined objects which will be displayed in the moDerivedProperties variable in the MoTable. The user must specify the names of derived properties in the following format .SYNTAX: propName1,propName2,...

tableOid.name: tableOid
tableOid.description: This variable states the oid of the table for the particular mo-type

tableName.name: tableName
tableName.description: This variable describes the table name

webNMSNumEvents.name: webNMSNumEvents
webNMSNumEvents.description: The total Number of Events in the AdventNet WebNMS system

webNMSNumAlerts.name: webNMSNumAlerts
webNMSNumAlerts.description: The total Number of Alerts in the AdventNet WebNMS system

webNMSEventsInBuffer.name: webNMSEventsInBuffer
webNMSEventsInBuffer.description: The Size of the Event Queue in the AdventNet WebNMS system

webNMSAlertsInBuffer.name: webNMSAlertsInBuffer
webNMSAlertsInBuffer.description: The Size of the Alert Queue in the AdventNet WebNMS system

alertUserPropNames.name: alertUserPropNames
alertUserPropNames.description: This variable indicates to the agent what all user property values the user would like to see in the alertUserProperties variable of the AlertTable This also provides for the facility of viewing all the user property-values by specifying the word 'all' . If the user needs to see only a few specific user property values ,then he needs to specify them explicitly SYNTAX1 all SYNTAX2 userPropName1,userPropName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2..

eventUserPropNames.name: eventUserPropNames
eventUserPropNames.description: This variable indicates to the agent what all user properties value the user would like to see in the eventUserProperties variable in the EventTable This also provides for the facility of viewing all the user property-values by specifying the word 'all' . If the user needs to see only a few specific user property values ,then he needs to specify them explicitly SYNTAX1 all SYNTAX2 userPropName1,userPropName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2..

alertTable.name: alertTable
alertTable.description: This table describes all the elements of the alert. This table has been deprecated since the AlertSource column is not an index column. This table has been replaced by AlarmTable.

alertEntry.name: alertEntry
alertEntry.description: An entry of the alert table

alertEntity.name: alertEntity
alertEntity.description: This variable states the unique source of the alert which uniquely identifies any alert in the table.This corresponds to the Entity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertOwnerName.name: alertOwnerName
alertOwnerName.description: This variable states the name of the owner of the alert.This corresponds to the OwnerName entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertCreateTime.name: alertCreateTime
alertCreateTime.description: This variable states the time of creation of the alert.This corresponds to the CreateTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertSource.name: alertSource
alertSource.description: This variable indicates the source of the alert i.e., from where the alert generated.This corresponds to the Source entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertModTime.name: alertModTime
alertModTime.description: This variable states the latest time at which the alert status was modified.This corresponds to the ModTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertSeverity.name: alertSeverity
alertSeverity.description: This variable describes the severity of the alert in integer format.This corresponds to the Severity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertPreviousSeverity.name: alertPreviousSeverity
alertPreviousSeverity.description: This variable states the previous severity of the alert.This corresponds to the PreviousSeverity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertCategory.name: alertCategory
alertCategory.description: This variable describes the category to which the alert belongs to, in a string form.This corresponds to the Category entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertUserProperties.name: alertUserProperties
alertUserProperties.description: This variable describes the values ot the user properties which the user specifies in the alertUserPropNames variable in the WebNMSFaultMib module. The values will be displayed in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2,...

eventTable.name: eventTable
eventTable.description: This table describes the events in the event database

eventEntry.name: eventEntry
eventEntry.description: An entry of the event Table

evtID.name: evtID
evtID.description: This variable is the unique id (primary key) of this event object.This corresponds to the Id entry in the Event Table in the database

evtSource.name: evtSource
evtSource.description: This variable is the source of the event.This corresponds to the Source entry in the Event Table in the database

evtEntity.name: evtEntity
evtEntity.description: This variable is the Entity (also known as Failure Object) of the Event.This corresponds to the Entity entry in the Event Table in the database

evtSeverity.name: evtSeverity
evtSeverity.description: This variable is the Severity of the Event object.This corresponds to the Severity entry in the Event Table in the database

evtCategory.name: evtCategory
evtCategory.description: This variable gives the category of the event, like Topology events or Threshold event etc. This corresponds to the Category entry in the Event Table in the database

evtTime.name: evtTime
evtTime.description: This variable is the time of occurrence (creation), in milliseconds, of this Event object. This corresponds to the Ttime entry in the Event Table in the database

evtText.name: evtText
evtText.description: This variable gives the descriptive text message of the event.This corresponds to the Text entry in the Event Table in the database

eventUserProperties.name: eventUserProperties
eventUserProperties.description: This variable describes the values ot the user properties which the user specifies in the eventUserPropNames variable The values will be displayed in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2,...

webNMSSeverityTable.name: webNMSSeverityTable
webNMSSeverityTable.description: This table shows the number of alarms of a particular severity.

severityName.name: severityName
severityName.description: This variable displays the name of severity like critical,major,minor etc.

numberOfAlarms.name: numberOfAlarms
numberOfAlarms.description: This variable displays the number of alarms of a particular severity.

alarmTable.name: alarmTable
alarmTable.description: This table describes various attributes of the NMS alarms. This is the replacement table for alertTable.This table has the following features other than those found in alertTable: 1. AlarmSource added as the first index along with AlarmOwnerName and AlarmEntity. 2. AlarmAssignedTo - a new column to describe the owner to whom the alarm assigned.

alarmSource.name: alarmSource
alarmSource.description: This variable indicates the source of the alarm i.e.,from where the alarm generated. This corresponds to the Source entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmOwnerName.name: alarmOwnerName
alarmOwnerName.description: This variable states the OwnerName for the alarm.This corresponds to the OwnerName entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmEntity.name: alarmEntity
alarmEntity.description: This variable states the unique name of each alarm which is used to identifies any alarm. This corresponds to the Entity field in the Alert Table in the database

alarmSeverity.name: alarmSeverity
alarmSeverity.description: This variable describes the severity of the alarm in integer format. This corresponds to the Severity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmPreviousSeverity.name: alarmPreviousSeverity
alarmPreviousSeverity.description: This variable states the previous severity of the alarm. This corresponds to the PreviousSeverity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmCreateTime.name: alarmCreateTime
alarmCreateTime.description: This variable states the time at which the alarm has been created. This corresponds to the CreateTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmModTime.name: alarmModTime
alarmModTime.description: This variable states the latest time at which the alarm status was modified. This corresponds to the ModTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmCategory.name: alarmCategory
alarmCategory.description: This variable describes the category to which the alarm belongs to, in a string form. This corresponds to the Category entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmAssignedTo.name: alarmAssignedTo
alarmAssignedTo.description: This variable describes the owner to whom the alarm has assigned. This corresponds to the Who entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmUserProperties.name: alarmUserProperties
alarmUserProperties.description: This variable describes the values of the user properties which the user specifies in the alertUserPropNames variable in the WebNMSFaultMib module. The values will be displayed in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2,...

numPollObjects.name: numPollObjects
numPollObjects.description: This variable displays the total number of PolledData objects currently present in the Polling engine.

numActivePollers.name: numActivePollers
numActivePollers.description: This variable displays the total number of active pollers at that time.

numThresholdObjects.name: numThresholdObjects
numThresholdObjects.description: This variable displays the total number of threshold objects available

pollTable.name: pollTable
pollTable.description: The table describes the polleddatas in the database

pollEntry.name: pollEntry
pollEntry.description: It describes the various entries of the performance table

pollid.name: pollid
pollid.description: This variable represents the id of the PolledData. It is assigned by the poll engine when the PolledData is created and it is a unique value for every PolledData.This corresponds to the Id entry in the PolledDataTable in the database

polldataName.name: polldataName
polldataName.description: This variable represents the name of the PolledData, which is a user assigned name for identification purposes.This corresponds to the Name entry in the PolledData Table in the database

oid.name: oid
oid.description: This variable represents the OID that is being polled for on the agent.This corresponds to the oid entry in the PolledData Table in the database

pollingInterval.name: pollingInterval
pollingInterval.description: This variable represents the polling interval of this PolledData.This corresponds to the Period entry in the PolledData Table in the database

failureCount.name: failureCount
failureCount.description: This variable represents the failureCount for this PolledData.This corresponds to the FailureCount entry in the PolledData Table in the database

failureThreshold.name: failureThreshold
failureThreshold.description: This variable represents the failureThreshold for this PolledData.This corresponds to the FailureThreshold entry in the PolledData Table in the database

timeToPoll.name: timeToPoll
timeToPoll.description: This variable states the time at which polling has to be done again.This corresponds to the TimeVal entry in the PolledData Table in the database

polledTime.name: polledTime
polledTime.description: This variable states the time at which the polling was done.This corresponds to the LastTimeValue entry in the PolledData Table in the database

agentName.name: agentName
agentName.description: This variable represents the Agent Name

thresholdTable.name: thresholdTable
thresholdTable.description: A table showing all data related to threshold objects

thresholdEntry.name: thresholdEntry
thresholdEntry.description: All the entries of the threshold table

thresholdObjectName.name: thresholdObjectName
thresholdObjectName.description: This variable states the name of the threshold object.

thresholdKind.name: thresholdKind
thresholdKind.description: This variable states whether the threshold is of type long,string or percentage.

thresholdMessage.name: thresholdMessage
thresholdMessage.description: This variable displays the message generated when the threshold occurs.

thresholdClearMessage.name: thresholdClearMessage
thresholdClearMessage.description: This variable displays the message to be generated on clearing of the threshold .

thresholdSeverity.name: thresholdSeverity
thresholdSeverity.description: The severity of the event generated.

thresholdCategory.name: thresholdCategory
thresholdCategory.description: This variable displays the category of this ThresholdObject. Category of the ThresholdObject represents the category in which the events will be generated in case of thresholds.

maxRows.name: maxRows
